website_summaries.verdict: A premium engine air filter with an affordable price tag. A good pick for high-performance vehicles.
pros: Heavy-duty engine air filter is meant for larger, more fuel-intensive engines that take in more air as they run
Filter is designed to last longer than other filter options
cons: Limited model compatibility since the filter is designed for high-performance vehicles

customer_reviews.title: Di it yourself!
customer_reviews.text: I replace the air filter myself once a year. The dealer is a total ripoff and the process is so simple. Fit perfectly for my car. I really like that Amazon lets my imput my car's info to make sure it's a match.
customer_reviews.author: kmitch

customer_reviews.title: Cheaper than name brand, yet quite functional
customer_reviews.text: It does work perfectly. I like to replace the air filter every 8000 miles even though I could replace it 10000 miles at least. However, compared to Fram extra guard, the folds are slightly shorter, meaning lesser surface area to filter. It is cheaper than Fram and Toyota OEM. It is definitely better quality than Toyota OEM. I switch back and forth between Fram and this brand.
customer_reviews.author: Win Thein

customer_reviews.title: Arrived in great condition.
customer_reviews.text: This filter perfectly fit my 2014 Toyota RAV4. I bought this filter last time and had no issues with it, so bought it again for regular replacement. Fits and works perfectly. Arrived in great condition.
